From: cpaglebbeek <cglebbeek@gmail.com>
Date: 2026-06-01
Subject: [PATCH 0002] Add -DEMSCRIPTEN=1 to CFLAGS in build-emscripten-sdl2

dosbox-x' build-emscripten-sdl2 script exports CXXFLAGS with -DEMSCRIPTEN=1
but CFLAGS (used for plain C files) lacks it. This causes a compile-fail
in src/hardware/snd_pc98/sound/opngenc.c where include/np2glue.h:40
triggers '#error byteorder not enough information' — the EMSCRIPTEN-define
gate for BYTESEX_LITTLE is never reached during C-compile.

Diagnose context: emsdk 5.0.7 + macOS Intel host (DOSHorse v0.0.3-Sutherland
Track B sub-step 3 / build-emscripten-sdl2 first run, 2026-06-01).

Upstream-first per P-DSH-01: this should be PR'd to joncampbell123/dosbox-x
as a 1-line fix. Tracking: TODO add to UPSTREAM_PR_QUEUE.md (te maken).

Target file:
  build-emscripten-sdl2

Lines changed: 1 (one CFLAGS line gets +' -DEMSCRIPTEN=1')
Total delta: +1 -1 (net +0)

---
 build-emscripten-sdl2 | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/build-emscripten-sdl2 b/build-emscripten-sdl2
--- a/build-emscripten-sdl2
+++ b/build-emscripten-sdl2
@@ -23,7 +23,7 @@ LD="emcc"
 LD_CXX="em++"
 AR="emar"
 RANLIB="emranlib"
-CFLAGS="-DEMTERPRETER_SYNC"
+CFLAGS="-DEMTERPRETER_SYNC -DEMSCRIPTEN=1"
 CXXFLAGS="-DEMSCRIPTEN=1 -DEMTERPRETER_SYNC -s USE_ZLIB=1 -s USE_LIBPNG=1 -s USE_SDL=2 -s USE_SDL_NET=2"
 LDFLAGS="-DEMSCRIPTEN=1 -DEMTERPRETER_SYNC -s USE_ZLIB=1 -s USE_LIBPNG=1 -s USE_SDL=2 -s USE_SDL_NET=2 -s FORCE_FILESYSTEM=1 -s ALLOW_MEMORY_GROWTH=1 -s TOTAL_MEMORY=100663296 -s ASYNCIFY -s ERROR_ON_UNDEFINED_SYMBOLS=0"
 export CC CXX LD LD_CXX AR RANLIB CFLAGS CXXFLAGS LDFLAGS
